        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 6:04PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 604 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Village, or 13 miles east of Magnolia, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Dorado, Norphlet, Village, Lisbon, Mount Holly, Wesson, Calhoun,
Ebenezer, Newell, Laughlin, Marysville, Cairo, Noxobe, Three Creeks,
Spotville, and Medlock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
